1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,851
It was easy for people I called to say, I'm not interested, and hang up.

2
00:00:05,601 --> 00:00:10,050
Every Monday morning back then, our sales manager held a sales meeting.

3
00:00:10,161 --> 00:00:14,211
It was a pretty inspirational affair, and it made me feel good.

4
00:00:14,321 --> 00:00:20,530
And what's more, I always seemed to arrange more demonstrations on Monday than on any other day.

5
00:00:20,881 --> 00:00:27,331
But the trouble was that little of Monday's inspiration carried over to Tuesday and the rest of the week.

6
00:00:27,601 --> 00:00:29,250
Then I got an idea.

7
00:00:29,601 --> 00:00:34,451
If the sales manager can pep me up, why can't I pep myself up?

8
00:00:34,641 --> 00:00:39,571
Why not give myself a pep talk just before I start making those phone calls?

9
00:00:39,841 --> 00:00:42,290
That day, I decided to try it.

10
00:00:42,561 --> 00:00:47,010
Without telling anyone, I walked out on the lot and found a vacant car.

11
00:00:47,201 --> 00:00:50,131
Then, for several minutes, I talked to myself.

12
00:00:50,321 --> 00:00:55,171
I told myself, I'm a good car salesman and I'm going to be the best.

13
00:00:55,361 --> 00:00:58,371
I sell good cars and I give good deals.

14
00:00:58,561 --> 00:01:02,770
The people I'm phoning need those cars and I'm going to sell them.

15
00:01:03,281 --> 00:01:07,571
Well, from the very beginning, this self-supercharging paid off.

16
00:01:07,761 --> 00:01:11,171
I felt so good, I didn't dread making those calls.

17
00:01:11,281 --> 00:01:12,770
I wanted to make them.

18
00:01:13,121 --> 00:01:17,651
I no longer go out on the lot and sit in a car to give myself a pep talk,

19
00:01:17,681 --> 00:01:19,571
but I still use the technique.

20
00:01:19,761 --> 00:01:26,851
Before I dial a number, I silently remind myself that I'm a top-notch salesman and I'm going to get results,

21
00:01:26,881 --> 00:01:27,811
and I do.

22
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:31,010
That's a pretty good idea, isn't it?

23
00:01:31,201 --> 00:01:34,851
To be on top, you've got to feel like you're on top.

24
00:01:35,121 --> 00:01:40,290
Give yourself a pep talk and discover how much bigger and stronger you feel.

25
00:01:41,361 --> 00:01:48,770
Recently, in a training program I conducted, each person was asked to give a ten-minute talk on being a leader.

26
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:52,290
One of the trainees gave a miserable presentation.

27
00:01:52,401 --> 00:01:55,811
His knees literally shook and his hands trembled.

28
00:01:55,921 --> 00:01:58,131
He forgot what he was going to say.

29
00:01:58,401 --> 00:02:03,730
After fumbling for five or six minutes, he sat down, thoroughly defeated.

30
00:02:04,401 --> 00:02:11,730
After the session, I spoke to him just long enough to ask him to be there fifteen minutes early at the next session.

31
00:02:12,321 --> 00:02:16,931
As promised, he was there fifteen minutes ahead of time for the next session.

32
00:02:17,121 --> 00:02:21,331
The two of us sat down to discuss his talk of the night before.

33
00:02:21,761 --> 00:02:29,891
I asked him to remember as clearly as he could exactly what he had thought about the five minutes just before he gave his talk.

34
00:02:30,721 --> 00:02:34,211
Well, I guess all I thought about was how scared I was.

35
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:36,851
I knew I was going to make a fool of myself.

36
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:39,091
I knew I was going to be a flop.

37
00:02:39,281 --> 00:02:43,490
I kept thinking, who am I to be talking about being a leader?

38
00:02:43,761 --> 00:02:48,770
I tried to remember what I was going to say, but all I could think about was failing.

39
00:02:49,201 --> 00:02:53,331
Right there, I injected, is the answer to your problem.

40
00:02:53,521 --> 00:02:58,290
Before you got up to talk, you gave yourself a terrible mental beating.

41
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:01,010
You convinced yourself that you would fail.

42
00:03:01,201 --> 00:03:04,211
Is it any wonder your talk didn't come off well?

43
00:03:04,401 --> 00:03:07,811
Instead of developing courage, you developed fear.

44
00:03:08,401 --> 00:03:12,931
Now this evening's session, I continued, starts in just four minutes.

45
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:14,931
Here's what I'd like you to do.

46
00:03:15,121 --> 00:03:18,290
Give yourself a pep talk for the next few minutes.

47
00:03:18,401 --> 00:03:24,131
Go in that vacant room across the hall and tell yourself, I'm going to give a great talk.

48
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:28,211
I've got something those people need to hear and I want to say.

49
00:03:28,561 --> 00:03:33,091
Keep repeating those sentences forcefully, with complete conviction.

50
00:03:33,281 --> 00:03:36,851
Then come into the conference room and give your talk again.

51
00:03:37,601 --> 00:03:40,530
I wish you could have been there to hear the difference.

52
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:46,691
That brief, self-administered, hard-hitting pep talk helped him to make a splendid speech.

53
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:47,971
The moral?

54
00:03:48,161 --> 00:03:50,691
Practice uplifting self-praise.

55
00:03:51,041 --> 00:03:53,971
Don't practice belittling self-punishment.

56
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:56,691
You are what you think you are.

57
00:03:56,801 --> 00:04:00,290
Think more of yourself and there is more of you.